,"  </tbody>\n","</table>\n","</div><br><label><b>dtype:</b> float64</label>"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":35}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## b Train n Test Set Split"],"metadata":{"id":"7ZKGTL85sTPK"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#splitting data into test and split datasets. 80:20 train to test ratio\n","inputs_train, inputs_test, targets_train, targets_test = train_test_split(\n","    loan_data.drop('good_bad',axis = 1), loan_data['good_bad'], test_size=0.2,\n","    random_state= 75)"],"metadata":{"id":"M-hAPPpmsWJy"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["inputs_train.shape"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"JubZpwNFsZGW","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1768891216066,"user_tz":-540,"elapsed":5,"user":{"displayName":"Young Mark","userId":"08915244444976601721"}},"outputId":"dfa1792c-5d8f-4378-ed4d-735582980414"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["(373028, 207)"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":37}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["inputs_test.shape"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"D3KLe7DXsdFj","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1768891216072,"user_tz":-540,"elapsed":4,"user":{"displayName":"Young Mark","userId":"08915244444976601721"}},"outputId":"6143de24-d9b5-4505-840f-2b14cc0baf02"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["(93257, 207)"]},"metadata":{},"execution_count":38}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## c Selecting test or train set for preproc."],"metadata":{"id":"20qcTEF_sg9a"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["#first run it for train set and then for test set for the preprocessing\n","df_inputs_prepr = inputs_train\n","df_targets_prepr = targets_train\n","#test set\n","#df_inputs_prepr = inputs_test\n","#df_targets_prepr = targets_test\n","\n","#next we will calculate Weight of Evidence (WoE)"],"metadata":{"id":"LheDiJH7sd8i"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["이산형 데이터 전처리의 핵심 기법인 **WoE(Weight of Evidence)** 와 **IV(Information Value)** 에 관한 내용\n","---\n","\n","# [L01] 4. 이산형 데이터 준비 - WoE 및 IV 계산\n","\n","모델의 예측력을 높이기 위해 **WoE(증거가중치)**와 **IV(정보가치)** 계산을 자동화하고, 이를 바탕으로 변수를 선택하는 과정을 진행합니다.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 📈 WoE (Weight of Evidence)\n","\n","WoE는 독립 변수가 종속 변수를 얼마나 잘 예측하는지를 나타내는 지표입니다.\n","\n","* **Positive WoE (+):** 우량 고객의 분포(Goods) > 불량 고객의 분포(Bads)\n","* **Negative WoE (-):** 우량 고객의 분포(Goods) < 불량 고객의 분포(Bads)\n","* **힌트:** 1보다 큰 수의 로그값은 양수이며, 1보다 작은 수의 로그값은 음수입니다.\n","\n","### 변수 그룹화 방법 (Classing)\n","\n","WoE 계산 시 그룹을 분류하는 두 가지 방법이 있습니다.\n","\n","1. **Fine Classing (세분화):** 연속형 독립 변수에 대해 10~20개의 구간(Bin)을 만들어 WoE와 IV를 계산합니다.\n","2. **Coarse Classing (粗분류):** WoE 점수가 유사한 인접한 카테고리들을 하나로 병합하여 모델을 단순화합니다.\n","\n","---\n","\n","## 📊 IV (Information Value)\n","\n","IV는 예측 모델에서 중요한 변수를 선택하는 데 유용한 기법입니다. 특정 독립 변수가 종속 변수를 설명하는 데 있어 얼마나 많은 정보를 제공하는지를 나타내며, 변수의 중요도 순위를 매기는 데 도움을 줍니다.\n","\n","### IV 계산 공식\n","\n","### IV 수치에 따른 예측력 평가 기준\n","\n","IV 값에 따라 해당 변수의 유용성을 다음과 같이 판단합니다.\n","\n","| IV 범위 | 예측력 (Predictive Power) |\n","| --- | --- |\n","| **0.02 미만** | 예측에 쓸모없음 (Not useful) |\n","| **0.02 ~ 0.1** | 낮은 예측력 (Weak) |\n","| **0.1 ~ 0.3** | 중간 정도의 예측력 (Medium) |\n","| **0.3 ~ 0.5** | 높은 예측력 (Strong) |\n","| **0.5 초과** | 의심스러운 예측력 (Suspicious) |\n"],"metadata":{"id":"ORhSYpfAsuTa"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Part 1 Discrete Variables: Dummy Variables"],"metadata":{"id":"NFzEUb_ps4Cq"}},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"id":"new_cell_1"},"source":["import pandas as pd\n","import numpy as np\n","\n","def woe_discrete(df, variable_name, target_name):\n","    # Calculate counts of good and bad for each category\n","    df_temp = pd.DataFrame(df.groupby(variable_name)[target_name].count())\n","    df_temp['good'] = df.groupby(variable_name)[target_name].sum()\n","    df_temp['bad'] = df_temp[target_name] - df_temp['good']\n","\n","    # Calculate overall good and bad counts\n","    overall_good = df_temp['good'].sum()\n","    overall_bad = df_temp['bad'].sum()\n","\n","    # Calculate proportions of good and bad for each category\n","    # Add a small epsilon to avoid division by zero or log(0)\n","    df_temp['good_prop'] = df_temp['good'] / overall_good\n","    df_temp['bad_prop'] = df_temp['bad'] / overall_bad\n","\n","    # Handle cases where proportions are zero by setting to a small positive value\n","    # This avoids issues with np.log(0) which results in -inf\n","    df_temp['good_prop'] = np.where(df_temp['good_prop'] == 0, 0.000001, df_temp['good_prop'])\n","    df_temp['bad_prop'] = np.where(df_temp['bad_prop'] == 0, 0.000001, df_temp['bad_prop'])\n","\n","    # Calculate WoE and IV\n","    df_temp['woe'] = np.log(df_temp['good_prop'] / df_temp['bad_prop'])\n","    df_temp['iv'] = (df_temp['good_prop'] - df_temp['bad_prop']) * df_temp['woe']\n","\n","    # Sort by WoE for better readability\n","    df_temp = df_temp.sort_values(by='woe')\n","    return df_temp"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["# Combine inputs and targets for WoE calculation\n","temp_df_for_woe = pd.concat([df_inputs_prepr, df_targets_prepr], axis=1)\n","# Calculate WoE for 'grade' using the combined DataFrame and the target column name 'good_bad'\n","df_temp = woe_discrete(temp_df_for_woe, 'grade', 'good_bad')\n","df_temp"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/","height":300},"id":"Pou_0GvvszWC","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1768891216411,"user_tz":-540,"elapsed":333,"user":{"displayName":"Young Mark","userId":"08915244444976601721"}},"outputId":"9f09f1b8-22d5-4587-cb0b-f8dfdce9d24d"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["       good_bad    good    bad  good_prop  bad_prop       woe        iv\n","grade                                                                  \n","G          2657    1995    662  